## by Beat KÃ¼ng

pacmdvolume is a command line tool to control the PulseAudio sound server. It shows sinks, sources, connected clients and controls their volume. It allows to change each channel's volume separately. This is useful especially for surround systems and the usage in scripts.


== compilation ==

requirements: 
	- pulseaudio (+ development files)

just run:
 $ make
to compile and run
 $ ./pacmdvolume
to print the usage



== miscellaneous ==

if you have any improvements or suggestions you are welcome to 
implement them and/or contact me


